    bibo:volume "4317" ;
    dc:creator "Lisi, Oscar" ;
    dc:date "2017" ;
    dc:title "Two new species of Eutardigrada from Victoria Land, Antarctica" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.885548>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.885550>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.885552>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.885554> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.885548>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Mixibius felix. sp. nov. A, Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus of the holotype (slide No. 4535). B, Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus of a paratype (slide No. 4539) in lateral view: the hook-shaped apophyses for the insertion of the stylet muscles are visible (the ventral indicated by arrow “ a ”, the dorsal by arrow “ b ”), both followed by a thickening of the buccal tube wall. C, Claws of the second pair of legs of a paratype (slide No. 4540); an accessory point of the external claw (arrow) is visible. D, Claws of the hind legs of a paratype (slide No. 4531). Scale bars = 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/885548/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.885550>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Acutuncus antarcticus. A, B: Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus (slide No. 5779); the peculiar shape (characteristic of the genus) of the apophyses for the insertion of the stylet muscles (arrows) is evident. C, Claws of the third pair of legs (slide No. 5779). D, Claws of the hind legs (slide No. 5774). Scale bars = 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/885550/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.885552>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. A – C, Holotype of Mixibius fueginus (slide No. 4335): A, Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus. B, Claws of the third pair of legs. C, Claws of the hind legs. Scale bars = 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/885552/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.885554>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Mixibius saracenus. A, Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus of holotype (slide No. 1701). B, Claws of the first and second pair of legs (slide No. 4099). C, Claws of the hind legs (slide No. 4099). Scale bars = 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/885554/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

